      "text": "Blood transfusion requires screening of donor blood for all of the following infections except:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Hepatitis C virus"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Dengue virus"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "HIV virus"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Hepatitis B virus"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Dengue fever </strong>is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5cc2d9fac616927772021889ee6d52\">viral</span> illness transmitted by <strong>Aedes mosquitoes</strong>. Unlike some other diseases listed, routine screening for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"75dc439beb16927771857bde5104df\">dengue</span> in donated blood is not typically performed. This is because mosquitoes primarily transmit <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"75dc439beb16927771857bde5104df\">dengue</span> rather than through blood transfusions.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Screening for transfusion-transmitted infections:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>The following infections can be transmitted by blood transfusion.</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:646px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Viral</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Bacterial</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Parasites</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Others</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Hepatitis (A, B, C, G)</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>HIV (I & II)</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>HTLV (I & II)</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>CMV</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>EBV</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Parvovirus B19</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Syphilis</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Malaria</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Babesiosis</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Trypanosoma cruzi</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Creutzfeldt-<br />\n\t\t\tJakob disease</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Plasma processing methods have been shown to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8bc8a6d0441692777190e9bed75e91\">inactivate</span> most recognized <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"aa279cf1f016927771903f195bb1b9\">infectious</span> organisms, except for <strong>non-lipid-enveloped viruses</strong> and <strong>prions.</strong></li>\n\t<li><strong>All clinically relevant blood components</strong> transmit <strong>prion disease</strong> following a<strong> single blood transfusion.</strong></li>\n\t<li><strong>Malaria</strong> can also be <strong>transmitted by most blood components</strong> (red cells, platelets, white-cell concentrates, cryoprecipitates, and frozen red cells after thawing and washing).\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>Transmission from single-donor FFP has not been reported.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li><strong>In India, the following five diseases are screened:</strong>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>HBV </strong><strong>(Option D)</strong></li>\n\t\t<li><strong>HCV </strong><strong>(Option A)</strong></li>\n\t\t<li><strong>HIV </strong><strong>(Option C)</strong></li>\n\t\t<li>Malaria</li>\n\t\t<li>Syphilis</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Screening for the diseases mentioned above is <strong>mandatory</strong>, and transfusing unscreened blood is a <strong>medical offence.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br />\n </p>",
